-- Geodynamics Share Sale May Raise Less Than A$100 Million Planned Earlier
-- James Paton
-- 2010-08-03T00:41:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/geodynamics-share-sale-may-raise-less-than-a-100-million-planned-earlier.html

          
          
             Geodynamics Ltd. plans to raise less
than the A$100 million it previously targeted in a share sale
expected later this year because of market uncertainty, Managing
Director Jack Hamilton said.  
 Geodynamics plans to begin producing power from a 25
megawatt plant and to demonstrate the projectâ€™s commercial
viability in early 2015 after a final investment decision in
2013, he said in an interview in Sydney. Hamilton, who
became interim managing director after Gerry Grove-White
resigned last month, said Geodynamics plans to name a permanent
replacement by the end of the year.  
